<title>NEW ZEALAND: Telecom announces split of its ADSs.</title>
<headline>Telecom announces split of its ADSs.</headline>
<dateline>WELLINGTON 1996-03-26</dateline>
<text>
<p>Telecom Corp of New Zealand on Wednesday said it was halving the number of shares in its American Depository Shares (ADS) into bundles of eight from 16 with effect from April 1.  </p>
<p>The change will be done via a two-for-one stock split with a record date of April 1 and a mailing date of April 8.</p>
<p>Ordinary shares will be unaffected.</p>
<p>Telecom said the move would encourage greater numbers of private individual shareholders to own shares because of the lower entry cost.</p>
<p>The current standard parcel of 100 ADSs costs more than US$7,000.</p>
<p>-- Wellington newsroom 64 4 4734 746</p>
